						<summary>

						<p>This is damaged and dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1478, Rākshasa, Śrāvaṇa, ba. 5, Guruvāra</hi> corresponding to <hi rend="bold">A.D. 1555 August 7, Wednesday,</hi> not Thursday, in the reign of <hi rend="bold">Sadāśiva-Mahārāya.</hi> It records that <hi rend="bold">Komaravīra,</hi> son of <hi rend="bold">Komaravīrayya</hi> of <hi rend="bold">Ānegondi,</hi> made a grant of land for the service of a god (name lost) in <hi rend="bold">Virūpākshapura.</hi></p>						

